Kenya Airways Passenger Numbers Increased 28%; Shares Rise

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-08-01T13:45:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-01/kenya-airways-passenger-numbers-grew-by-28-in-three-months-through-june.html
Kenya Airways Ltd. (KNAL) , sub-Saharan
Africa’s third-biggest airline, said passenger numbers grew 28
percent in the three months through June to 850,908.  Cargo tonnage increased 20 percent to 15,286 metric tons,
the Nairobi-based company said in a statement e-mailed by the
city’s stock exchange today.  Passengers within Kenya increased 65 percent to 184,845
while the number of travelers to the  Middle East , Far East and
Asia climbed 31 percent, according to the statement.  The company’s shares gained for a second day, adding 0.8
percent to 32.75 shillings by the 3 p.m. close in the capital,
Nairobi.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  